==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extrinsic
<hw>Ex*trin"sic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>extrinsecus</ets>; <ets>exter</ets> on the outside +
<ets>secus</ets> otherwise, beside; akin to E. <ets>second</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>extrins⟦egrave⟧que</ets>. See <er>Exterior</er>,
<er>Second</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not contained in or belonging
to a body; external; outward; unessential; -- opposed to
<ant>intrinsic</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>extrinsic</qex> aids of education and of artificial
culture.</q> <rj><qau>I. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Attached partly to an organ or
limb and partly to some other part; -- said of certain groups of
muscles. Opposed to <contr>intrinsic</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extrinsical</ent>⟦br⟧
